lead_paragraph: TYLER--Jean Cadwell, of New York City died February 3, 2016. She was born to Cadwell Tyler II and Jean Keller Tyler December 15, 1940, in Goshen, NY. A graduate of Wellesley College, she spent a career of almost 30 years in health education at New York City's Maternity, Infant Care, and Family Planning Projects (MIC), including serving as Director of Health Education and finally as Director of Communications and Education. She helped found and was president of the Greater New York Chapter of the Society of Public Health Educators. Services will be April 30, 2016, at 11am at St. James Episcopal Church, Goshen, NY. Memorial contributions can be made to: City Harvest (www.cityharvest.org); the Doe Fund (www.doe.org); or to a charity of the donor's choice. 1/3
